  "text": "• Treadmill walking • Heel raises • Trampette walking/jogging • Sit to stands • Toe-walking • Step ups 5.2.1.2. CAD specific exercise. The conditioning phase for CAD patients will consist of the same circuit of cardiovascular exercises as the PAD Fig. 3 . Contraindications for outpatient cardiac rehabilitation -american college of sports medicine [CITATION_1] . Fig. 4 . This shows the Intermittent Claudication Rating Scale which will be used by patients to grade the amount of claudication pain they experience during the GTT and SEP. Taken from ACCPVR Guidelines for Cardiac Rehabilitation and Secondary Prevention Programs (2013).",
